race.comment: Tough on paper. LOVE TO ALL (9) resumed over 1100m at Gatton and just missed at big odds. She's much improved but has a wide gate to manage today. Regardless will strip fitter and is a winning chance with average luck. GERRY'S PICK (11) races forward and is threatening a win. Comes back 200m and in this lineup he can get into the money. EJAY'S FIREFOX (10) resumes for the Wallace yard and is up to this if presented forward. Has an inside gate and a handy 2kg claim and should give a big sight. BLACK 'N' DEADLY (12) resumes and has trialled well enough at Ipswich. Has an awkward barrier, but is proven fresh and has a handy 3kg claim. He can't be ruled out in an open race.
